zhnSystem.name: zhnSystem

revisions.description: Added new sysSnmpProvisioningLock and sysSnmpProvisioningChange objects.
Added new zhnWanBackupTable, dnsProxyHostEntryTable, and zhnDnsProxyHostMaxHostEntries objects.
Removed comma in the end of the last line of the enum definitions.
Added: - Bootloader, FW, and alternate FW versions - SNTP objects - User Access Login objects - Power-shedding objects - Syslog objects - coldStart, warmStart and enterprise trap filtering objects
Changed the name of sysContact to zhnSysContact and sysLocation to zhnSysLocation. And, added scalar objects sysSystemClockSource, sysEthernetTransmitClockSource, and sysDs1ClockSourcePort.
General MIB file cleanup. Also added not-applicable values to some of the textual convention objects.
Added Pseudo-Wire Emulation (PWE) System Timing objects.
Added Trap Manager Table, Community String Table, zhnSysLocation and zhnSysContact objects.

CSMI.name: CSMI
CSMI.description: Pseudo Wire Clock Synchronization Mode Items

SysFirmwareAction.name: SysFirmwareAction
SysFirmwareAction.description: Action to take on the current firmware version.

SysAdminStatus.name: SysAdminStatus
SysAdminStatus.description: Administrative status options for various system services, like syslog and power-shedding.

SysLogLevel.name: SysLogLevel
SysLogLevel.description: SysLog logging level options, per RFC 3164.

SysSntpTimeZones.name: SysSntpTimeZones
SysSntpTimeZones.description: Simple Network Timing Protocol time zones.

IPInterfaceAddressingTypeValues.name: IPInterfaceAddressingTypeValues
IPInterfaceAddressingTypeValues.description: The addressing method used to assign the LAN-side IP Address. Enumeration of: Unknown Unconfigured Default DHCP Static PPPoE OMCI

BasicAddressingTypeValues.name: BasicAddressingTypeValues
BasicAddressingTypeValues.description: Enumeration of: DHCP - The DNS information is obtained via DHCP Static - The DNS information is manually provisioned

numberOfMacAddresses.name: numberOfMacAddresses
numberOfMacAddresses.description: Number of MAC Address sequentially defined in the Unit starting at the MAC Base Address.

wifiNetworkType.name: wifiNetworkType
wifiNetworkType.description: Defines the Network Type or Mode of the Unit, i.e. Mesh or Base Station

locationLatitude.name: locationLatitude
locationLatitude.description: The latitude of the unit's location represented in degrees decimal. The format of the location's latitude is: [+ | -]ddd.dddddddd where + indicates north - indicates south d is a decimal digit (0 <= d <= 9) Valid range is -90 to +90 degrees.

locationLongitude.name: locationLongitude
locationLongitude.description: The longitude of the unit's location represented in degrees decimal. The format of the location's longitude is: [+ | -]ddd.dddddddd where + indicates east - indicates west d is a decimal digit (0 <= d <= 9) Valid range is -180 to +180 degrees.

zhnSystemAction.name: zhnSystemAction
zhnSystemAction.description: Action parameter to handle the action on other scalars.

zhnSysLocation.name: zhnSysLocation
zhnSysLocation.description: System location. This object is synonomous with the MIB II system sysLocation object.

zhnSysContact.name: zhnSysContact
zhnSysContact.description: System contact. This object is synonomous with the MIB II system sysContact object.

sysTransmitClockSource.name: sysTransmitClockSource
sysTransmitClockSource.description: T1 Clock source for PWE device. Since both T1/E1 interfaces will be required to have the same source, this object will replace the dsx1TransmitClockSource object in the DS1-MIB. This object is not supported by ZNID devices.

sysLocalTimingReference.name: sysLocalTimingReference
sysLocalTimingReference.description: Source of the sysTransmitClockSource when set to Local. This object is not supported by ZNID devices.

sysSynchronizationMode.name: sysSynchronizationMode
sysSynchronizationMode.description: Determines the method of ensuring Service Clock synchronization between the Source and Remote PWE devices.

sysSynchronousEthernet.name: sysSynchronousEthernet
sysSynchronousEthernet.description: Determines whether or not to use the 25MHz clock derived from the Synchronous Ethernet Port. This object is not supported by ZNID devices.

sysClockMode.name: sysClockMode
sysClockMode.description: Determines the mode for which the PWE chip will be initialized.

sysCfgDBAction.name: sysCfgDBAction
sysCfgDBAction.description: Perform an action on the configuration database.

sysSystemClockSource.name: sysSystemClockSource
sysSystemClockSource.description: Determines the system-level clock mode for ZNID devices. uplink - the system will recover its clock from the configured uplink (e.g. GPON, SPF1, SFP2, etc.). ds1 - the system will recover its clock from the configured sysDs1ClockSourcePort. ieee1588 - the system will recover clock from the on-board 1588 clock circuitry.

sysEthernetTransmitClockSource.name: sysEthernetTransmitClockSource
sysEthernetTransmitClockSource.description: Determines the transmit clock source for all ethernet ports requiring a clock. internal - all ethernet ports will recover clock from the local oscillator. systemClock - all ethernet ports will recover clock from the sysSystemClockSource.

sysDs1ClockSourcePort.name: sysDs1ClockSourcePort
sysDs1ClockSourcePort.description: The interface name for the DS1 port providing transmit clock when the sysSystemClockSource is set to ds1.

sysFirmwareVersion.name: sysFirmwareVersion
sysFirmwareVersion.description: The version of firmware the system is currently running.

sysAltFirmwareVersion.name: sysAltFirmwareVersion
sysAltFirmwareVersion.description: The alternate firmware version currently stored in system flash.

sysRestoreAltFirmwareVersion.name: sysRestoreAltFirmwareVersion
sysRestoreAltFirmwareVersion.description: This object can be used to restore the version of firmware to the alternate firmware version currently stored in flash.

sysSnmpProvisioningLock.name: sysSnmpProvisioningLock
sysSnmpProvisioningLock.description: This object can be set by an SNMP client to indicate that system configuration is in progress. All other SNMP clients will be locked out while this is set to true. This lock will timeout after 30 seconds.

sysSnmpProvisioningChange.name: sysSnmpProvisioningChange
sysSnmpProvisioningChange.description: This object can be incremented by SNMP clients to indicate a sysCfgDBAction save has taken place.

numberOfBoards.name: numberOfBoards
numberOfBoards.description: Number of boards in the Unit with Name, Part Number, Serial Number and Revision Number values

boardDescriptorTable.name: boardDescriptorTable
boardDescriptorTable.description: Table of boards: Name, Part Number, Serial Number and Revision Number values

boardDescriptorEntry.name: boardDescriptorEntry
boardDescriptorEntry.description: Table of boards: Name, Part Number, Serial Number and Revision Number values

boardName.name: boardName
boardName.description: Name of the Board as created by the system

boardPartNumber.name: boardPartNumber
boardPartNumber.description: Part Number of the Board. Read from the board

boardSerialNumber.name: boardSerialNumber
boardSerialNumber.description: Serial Number of the Board. Read from the board

boardRevision.name: boardRevision
boardRevision.description: Revision Number of the Board. Read from the board

numberOfPlds.name: numberOfPlds
numberOfPlds.description: Number of PLDs in the Unit with Name and Version Number values

pldDescriptorTable.name: pldDescriptorTable
pldDescriptorTable.description: Table of boards: Name, Part Number, Serial Number and Revision Number values

pldDescriptorEntry.name: pldDescriptorEntry
pldDescriptorEntry.description: Table of boards: Name, Part Number, Serial Number and Revision Number values

pldName.name: pldName
pldName.description: Name of the PLD as created by the system

pldVersion.name: pldVersion
pldVersion.description: PLD Software Version. Read from the PLD

numberOfRadios.name: numberOfRadios
numberOfRadios.description: Number of Radios in the Unit

numberOfEthernetLikeInterfaces.name: numberOfEthernetLikeInterfaces
numberOfEthernetLikeInterfaces.description: Number of Ethernet Like Interfaces with Name, Type and Subtype

ethernetlikeInterfaceEntry.name: ethernetlikeInterfaceEntry
ethernetlikeInterfaceEntry.description: Table of ethernet-like interfaces having Name, type, subtype, number of ports, line power and number of pairs with power

etherIndex.name: etherIndex
etherIndex.description: Index of the Ethernet Like Interface (zero relative)

etherName.name: etherName
etherName.description: Name of the ethernet Like Interface as created by the system

etherNumberOfPorts.name: etherNumberOfPorts
etherNumberOfPorts.description: Number of Ports on the Ethernet interface

etherLinePower.name: etherLinePower
etherLinePower.description: Line Power Type on this Ethernet Interface

etherPowerPairs.name: etherPowerPairs
etherPowerPairs.description: Number of line Pairs providing power on the Ethernet interface

numberOfTemperatureSensors.name: numberOfTemperatureSensors
numberOfTemperatureSensors.description: Number of Temperature Sensors in the Unit

temperatureSensorTable.name: temperatureSensorTable
temperatureSensorTable.description: Table of Temperature Sensors: Name, Maximum, and Minimum values

temperatureSensorEntry.name: temperatureSensorEntry
temperatureSensorEntry.description: Table of Temperature Sensors: Name, Maximum, and Minimum values

temperatureSensorName.name: temperatureSensorName
temperatureSensorName.description: Name of the ethernet Like Interface as created by the system

powerSupplyType.name: powerSupplyType
powerSupplyType.description: Type of Power Supply that the unit is using

numberOfCommunities.name: numberOfCommunities
numberOfCommunities.description: Number of SNMP Communities configured in the Unit

zhnCommunityTable.name: zhnCommunityTable
zhnCommunityTable.description: This table is used to set the various configuration parameters for a particular community.

zhnCommunityTableEntry.name: zhnCommunityTableEntry
zhnCommunityTableEntry.description: This object corresponds to an entry in the community table.

communityName.name: communityName
communityName.description: This object corresponds to the SNMP community string.

communityType.name: communityType
communityType.description: The access type of the community string. The default value of this object should be read-only(1).

communityRowStatus.name: communityRowStatus
communityRowStatus.description: When written, this object can be used to createAndGo(4) or destroy(6) a row from the table. A rowStatus value of notInService(2) will also destroy a row. RowStatus values of active(1), notReady(3), and createAndWait(5) are ignored.

numberOfTrapManagers.name: numberOfTrapManagers
numberOfTrapManagers.description: Number of Trap Managers configured in the Unit

zhnDefaultTrapCommunity.name: zhnDefaultTrapCommunity
zhnDefaultTrapCommunity.description: This object corresponds to the default trap community string. The default trap community string will be used when a community name is not configured for a particular trap manager.

zhnTrapTypeLinkUpDown.name: zhnTrapTypeLinkUpDown
zhnTrapTypeLinkUpDown.description: Enable or disable all link up/down traps.

zhnTrapTypeAuthFailure.name: zhnTrapTypeAuthFailure
zhnTrapTypeAuthFailure.description: Enable or disable the generation of authorization failure traps.

zhnTrapTypeConfigChange.name: zhnTrapTypeConfigChange
zhnTrapTypeConfigChange.description: Enable or disable the generation of configuration change traps. This object is not supported by ZNID devices. Rather, the only mechanism to disable the generation of configuration change traps in a ZNID device is to disable the generation of all enterprise traps via the zhnTrapTypeEnterpise object.

zhnTrapManagerInfoTable.name: zhnTrapManagerInfoTable
zhnTrapManagerInfoTable.description: This table is used to set the trap destination address for a particular community.

zhnTrapManagerInfoTableEntry.name: zhnTrapManagerInfoTableEntry
zhnTrapManagerInfoTableEntry.description: This object corresponds to an entry in the community trap address info table.

trapDestination.name: trapDestination
trapDestination.description: The IP Address of the destination to which a trap must be sent.

trapCommunityName.name: trapCommunityName
trapCommunityName.description: This object corresponds to the trap community string. If not specified, the trapCommunityName will be set to the zhnDefaultTrapCommunity object.

trapVersion.name: trapVersion
trapVersion.description: The trap types automatically supported by net-snmp and enabled/disabled in snmpd.conf. If not specified, the trapVersion will be set the default value of v2c.

trapPort.name: trapPort
trapPort.description: The udp/tcp port number to which a trap must be sent. If not specified, the trapPort will be set the default value of 162.

trapRowStatus.name: trapRowStatus
trapRowStatus.description: When written, this object can be used to createAndGo(4) or destroy(6) a row from the table. A rowStatus value of notInService(2) will also destroy a row. RowStatus values of active(1), notReady(3), and createAndWait(5) are ignored.

zhnTrapTypeColdStart.name: zhnTrapTypeColdStart
zhnTrapTypeColdStart.description: Enable or disable the generation of coldstart traps. A coldstart trap is generated each time the device is restarted.

zhnTrapTypeWarmStart.name: zhnTrapTypeWarmStart
zhnTrapTypeWarmStart.description: Enable or disable the generation of warmstart traps. A warmstart trap is generated each time the device's SNMP agent is restarted.

zhnTrapTypeEnterprise.name: zhnTrapTypeEnterprise
zhnTrapTypeEnterprise.description: Enable or disable the generation of all enterprise traps.

zhnFixedCommunityTable.name: zhnFixedCommunityTable
zhnFixedCommunityTable.description: This table is used to configure a read-only and a read-write community.

zhnFixedCommunityTableEntry.name: zhnFixedCommunityTableEntry
zhnFixedCommunityTableEntry.description: This object corresponds to an entry in the fixed community table.

fixedCommunityName.name: fixedCommunityName
fixedCommunityName.description: This object corresponds to the SNMP community string.

fixedCommunityType.name: fixedCommunityType
fixedCommunityType.description: The access type of the community string. The default value of this object should be read-only(1).

fixedCommunityRowStatus.name: fixedCommunityRowStatus
fixedCommunityRowStatus.description: When written, this object is ignored. When read, a value of active(1) or notReady(3) will be returned.

sysLogAdminStatus.name: sysLogAdminStatus
sysLogAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable the Syslog service.

sysLogLocalLogLevel.name: sysLogLocalLogLevel
sysLogLocalLogLevel.description: SysLog local log level options, per RFC 3164. All logged events with a severity at or greater than this level will be logged to the local log file. Note, the local log file is not persistent across system reboots.

sysLogRemoteLogLevel.name: sysLogRemoteLogLevel
sysLogRemoteLogLevel.description: SysLog remote log level options, per RFC 3164. All logged events with a severity at or greater that this level will be sent to a remote Syslog server if the remote server address is configured and a route exists to the remote server.

sysLogDisplayLogLevel.name: sysLogDisplayLogLevel
sysLogDisplayLogLevel.description: SysLog log level options, per RFC 3164 for the display of log messages via a web browser. All logged events with a severity level at or greater than this level will be displayed.

sysLogMode.name: sysLogMode
sysLogMode.description: SysLog logging mode of operation: local(1), -- Log messages only to the local, non-persistent log file remote(2), -- Log messages only to a remote syslog server both(3), -- Log messages to both a local log file and a remote syslog server

sysLogRemoteServerAddress.name: sysLogRemoteServerAddress
sysLogRemoteServerAddress.description: The IP address of the remote syslog server.

sysLogRemoteServerPort.name: sysLogRemoteServerPort
sysLogRemoteServerPort.description: The UDP port to use to transfer syslog messages to the remote syslog server.

sntpAdminStatus.name: sntpAdminStatus
sntpAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable the SNTP client.

sntpOperStatus.name: sntpOperStatus
sntpOperStatus.description: Current operational status of the SNTP client.

sntpServer1.name: sntpServer1
sntpServer1.description: The domain name or IP address of the first SNTP server with which to synchronize the system time.

sntpServer2.name: sntpServer2
sntpServer2.description: The domain name or IP address of the second SNTP server with which to synchronize the system time.

sntpServer3.name: sntpServer3
sntpServer3.description: The domain name or IP address of the third SNTP server with which to synchronize the system time.

sntpServer4.name: sntpServer4
sntpServer4.description: The domain name or IP address of the fourth SNTP server with which to synchronize the system time.

sntpServer5.name: sntpServer5
sntpServer5.description: The domain name or IP address of the fifth SNTP server with which to synchronize the system time.

sntpCurrentDateAndTime.name: sntpCurrentDateAndTime
sntpCurrentDateAndTime.description: Indicates the current date and time.

adminUserName.name: adminUserName
adminUserName.description: The username required to login as the system administrator. This user has unrestricted access to change and view all configuration, status and test parameters.

adminPassword.name: adminPassword
adminPassword.description: The password required to login as the system administrator. This field cannot contain a SPACE and is returned as a string of asterisks.

supportUserName.name: supportUserName
supportUserName.description: The username required to login to support the system. This user has access to system parameters required to maintain the system and run diagnostic tests.

supportPassword.name: supportPassword
supportPassword.description: The password required to login to support the system. This field cannot contain a SPACE and is returned as a string of asterisks.

userUserName.name: userUserName
userUserName.description: The username required to login as a general user of the system. This user can view configuration settings and statistics, as well as, update the system's software.

userPassword.name: userPassword
userPassword.description: The password required to login as a general user of the system. field cannot contain a SPACE and is returned as a string of asterisks.

powerSheddingAdminStatus.name: powerSheddingAdminStatus
powerSheddingAdminStatus.description: Configuration of parameters for the power-shedding feature. The power-shedding objects are only supported by systems that include on-board power-management circuitry. When the system detects that it is running on battery power, it has the option to shut down all support (excluding the voice over IP telephone service).The power-shedding administrative state will enable or disable the power-shedding feature.

powerSheddingShutdownDelay.name: powerSheddingShutdownDelay
powerSheddingShutdownDelay.description: The shutdown delay is the time delay, in minutes, after AC power is lost, before shutting down non-voice services.

powerSheddingRestoreDelay.name: powerSheddingRestoreDelay
powerSheddingRestoreDelay.description: The restore delay is the time delay, in minutes, after AC power is restored before switching on the services that were shut down due to the power loss.

sysFirewallEnable.name: sysFirewallEnable
sysFirewallEnable.description: Enables or disables the firewall feature for the entire system.

sysFirewallTcpSynCookies.name: sysFirewallTcpSynCookies
sysFirewallTcpSynCookies.description: Enables or disables the TCP SYNCookie protection against SYN flooding denial-of-service attack.

sysDNSAddressingType.name: sysDNSAddressingType
sysDNSAddressingType.description: Type of IP interface addressing method used to reach the DNS.

sysDNSDHCPSource.name: sysDNSDHCPSource
sysDNSDHCPSource.description: Name of the interface used by the DHCP Client to obtain DNS information.

sysDNSPrimaryIPAddress.name: sysDNSPrimaryIPAddress
sysDNSPrimaryIPAddress.description: Primary Address of DNS when the addressing type is set to Static.

sysDNSSecondaryIPAddress.name: sysDNSSecondaryIPAddress
sysDNSSecondaryIPAddress.description: Secondary Address of DNS when the addressing type is set to Static.

zhnDnsProxyHostMaxHostEntries.name: zhnDnsProxyHostMaxHostEntries
zhnDnsProxyHostMaxHostEntries.description: The maximum number of host entries in the DnsProxyHostObjectTable.

zhnDnsProxyHostTable.name: zhnDnsProxyHostTable
zhnDnsProxyHostTable.description: This table is used to configure a DNS Proxy Host entry.

zhnDnsProxyHostEntry.name: zhnDnsProxyHostEntry
zhnDnsProxyHostEntry.description: This object corresponds to an entry in the DNS Proxy Host table.

dnsProxyHostIndex.name: dnsProxyHostIndex
dnsProxyHostIndex.description: Index into the DNS Proxy Host table

dnsProxyHostIPAddress.name: dnsProxyHostIPAddress
dnsProxyHostIPAddress.description: The local proxy host IP address.

dnsProxyHostName.name: dnsProxyHostName
dnsProxyHostName.description: The domain name assigned to the host IP address.

dnsProxyRowStatus.name: dnsProxyRowStatus
dnsProxyRowStatus.description: Create or destroy a DNS Proxy Host. Upon creation, the dnsProxyHostIPAddress must be provided.

failoverTimer.name: failoverTimer
failoverTimer.description: The WAN Failover Timer is used to determine how long (in seconds) the Fiber uplink interface must be operationally DOWN before a USB Cellular WAN Backup connection will be initiated. The Default value is 0 seconds, which DISABLES this feature. The recommended value to enable this feature is 60 seconds.

restoralTimer.name: restoralTimer
restoralTimer.description: The WAN Restoral Timer is used to determine how long (in seconds) the Fiber uplink interface must remain in an operational UP condition before the Cellular Backup connection will be terminated and the traffic that was being forwarded out the USB interface is forwarded to the 5xx GEM instead. The default value is 60 seconds.

backupDataVlan.name: backupDataVlan
backupDataVlan.description: This is the Internet Access VLAN (GEM 5xx), which is the only service that can be backed up using the USB Cellular modem.

cellularPinNumber.name: cellularPinNumber
cellularPinNumber.description: A 4 digit PIN code used to unlock the SIM card. For GPRS/UMTS networks, *99# is typically used. For CDMA/EVDO networks, #777 is typically used.

cellularDataNumber.name: cellularDataNumber
cellularDataNumber.description: This is the number that the USB modem will dial to establish a cellular a cellular data connection. For GPRS/UMTS networks, *99# is typically used. For CDMA/EVDO networks, #777 is typically used.

atInitCommands.name: atInitCommands
atInitCommands.description: AT initialization command strings, if needed.

accessPointName.name: accessPointName
accessPointName.description: The Access Point Name (APN) for connections to the GPRS/UMTS network. This should be provided by the ISP. In North America, 3G cellular carriers do not require an APN.

chapPapUsername.name: chapPapUsername
chapPapUsername.description: Required for CHAP or PAP authentication. This configuration item should be left blank if CHAP or PAP is not used.

chapPapPassword.name: chapPapPassword
chapPapPassword.description: Required for CHAP or PAP authentication. This configuration item should be left blank if CHAP or PAP is not used.

connectionTimeout.name: connectionTimeout
connectionTimeout.description: Specifies the duration of inactivity in seconds before the cellular data call will automatically terminate. A new call will be initiated automatically when a packet must be sent upstream on the designated VLAN if the WAN uplink is still Operationally Down. A value of 0 will DISABLE the Connection Timeout feature.

backupIpAddressMode.name: backupIpAddressMode
backupIpAddressMode.description: The WAN IP Address, Default Gateway IP Address, Subnet Mask and DNS Server IP Address must all be defined for the USB Cellular Backup connection. When IP Address Mode is set to DHCP, a DHCP Request will be sent upstream after the Cellular Data Connection has been established to acquire this information dynamically. When the WAN Backup IP Addess Mode is set to Static, this information ust be statically configured.

backupIpAddress.name: backupIpAddress
backupIpAddress.description: The IP Address to be used on the WAN uplink interface of a Cellular Backhaul connection. This parameter is acquired dynamically in DHCP mode and only configurable if the BackupIpAddressMode is Static.

backupDefaultGateway.name: backupDefaultGateway
backupDefaultGateway.description: The IP Address of the Default Gateway to be used on the WAN uplink interface of a Cellular Backhaul connection. This parameter is acquired dynamically in DHCP mode and only configurable if the BackupIpAddressMode is Static.

backupSubnetMask.name: backupSubnetMask
backupSubnetMask.description: The Subnet Mask to be used on the WAN uplink interface of a Cellular Backhaul connection. This parameter is acquired dynamically in DHCP mode and only configurable if the BackupIpAddressMode is Static.

backupPrimaryDns.name: backupPrimaryDns
backupPrimaryDns.description: The IP Address of the Primary DNS Server to be used on the WAN uplink interface of a Cellular Backhaul connection. This parameter is acquired dynamically in DHCP mode and only configurable if the BackupIpAddressMode is Static.

backupSecondaryDns.name: backupSecondaryDns
backupSecondaryDns.description: The IP Address of the Secondary DNS Server to be used on the WAN uplink interface of a Cellular Backhaul connection. This parameter is acquired dynamically in DHCP mode and only configurable if the BackupIpAddressMode is Static.

sysTr69cConfigLoggingSOAP.name: sysTr69cConfigLoggingSOAP
sysTr69cConfigLoggingSOAP.description: Enable or disable showing SOAP messages on serial console and local TR69 Client log file.

sysTr69cConfigConnectionRequestAuthentic.name: sysTr69cConfigConnectionRequestAuthentication
sysTr69cConfigConnectionRequestAuthentic.description: Enable or disable connection request authentication.

sysTr69cServerURL.name: sysTr69cServerURL
sysTr69cServerURL.description: URL for the CPE to connect to the ACS using the CPE WAN Management Protocol. This parameter MUST be in the form of a valid HTTP or HTTPS URL. The host portion of this URL is used by the CPE for server-side certificate authentication when using SSL or TLS.

sysTr69cServerLastConnectedURL.name: sysTr69cServerLastConnectedURL
sysTr69cServerLastConnectedURL.description: This value records the last URL which connected successfully to the TR69 client.

sysTr69cServerUsername.name: sysTr69cServerUsername
sysTr69cServerUsername.description: Username used to authenticate the CPE when making a connection to the ACS using the CPE WAN Management Protocol. This username is used only for HTTP-based authentication of the CPE.

sysTr69cServerPassword.name: sysTr69cServerPassword
sysTr69cServerPassword.description: Password used to authenticate the CPE when making a connection to the ACS using the CPE WAN Management Protocol. This username is used only for HTTP-based authentication of the CPE. When read by an ACS, this parameter returns an empty string, regardless of the value.

sysTr69cServerPeriodicInformEnable.name: sysTr69cServerPeriodicInformEnable
sysTr69cServerPeriodicInformEnable.description: When set to TRUE, the CPE will periodically send CPE information to the TR69 Server using the Inform method calls.

sysTr69cServerPeriodicInformInterval.name: sysTr69cServerPeriodicInformInterval
sysTr69cServerPeriodicInformInterval.description: The duration in seconds of the interval for which the CPE MUST attempt to connect with the ACS and call the Inform method if PeriodicInform-Enable is true.

sysTr69cServerParameterKey.name: sysTr69cServerParameterKey
sysTr69cServerParameterKey.description: ParameterKey provides the ACS a reliable and extensible means to track changes made by the ACS. The value of ParameterKey MUST be equal to the value of the ParameterKey argument from the most recent successful SetParameterValues, AddObject, or DeleteObject method call from the ACS. The CPE MUST set ParameterKey to the value specified in the corresponding method arguments if and only if the method completes successfully and no fault response is generated. If a method call does not complete successfully implying that the changes requested in the method did not take effect, the value of ParameterKey MUST NOT be modified. The CPE MUST only modify the value of ParameterKey as a result of SetParameterValues, AddObject, DeleteObject, or due to a factory reset. On factory reset, the value of ParameterKey MUST be set to empty.

sysTr69cServerBoundIfName.name: sysTr69cServerBoundIfName
sysTr69cServerBoundIfName.description: Name of the WAN interface that the TR69 client should use when establishing communications with the ACS.

sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestURL.name: sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestURL
sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestURL.description: HTTP URL for an ACS to make a Connection Request notification to the CPE. In the form: http://host:port/path. The host portion of the URL MAY be the IP address for the management interface of the CPE in lieu of a host name.

sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestUsername.name: sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestUsername
sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestUsername.description: Username used to authenticate an ACS making a Connection Request to the CPE.

sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestPassword.name: sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestPassword
sysTr69cServerConnectionRequestPassword.description: Password used to authenticate an ACS making a Connection Request to the CPE. When read by an ACS, this parameter returns an empty string, regardless of the actual value.

sysTr69cServerUpgradesManaged.name: sysTr69cServerUpgradesManaged
sysTr69cServerUpgradesManaged.description: Indicates whether or not the ACS will manage upgrades for the CPE. If true (1), the CPE SHOULD not use other means other than the ACS to seek out available upgrades. If false (0), the CPE MAY use other means for this purpose.

zhnSystemCompliance.name: zhnSystemCompliance
zhnSystemCompliance.description: The Compliance statement for SNMP entities which manage the display of Zhone System Information

zhnSystemActiveGroup.name: zhnSystemActiveGroup
zhnSystemActiveGroup.description: A collection of System Information objects that are required for the device to be functional

zhnSystemTablesItems.name: zhnSystemTablesItems
zhnSystemTablesItems.description: The table items for the device that are filled in when the table is present

zhnSystemConfigItems.name: zhnSystemConfigItems
zhnSystemConfigItems.description: The collection of configurable scalar system objects.

zhnSystemTrapItems.name: zhnSystemTrapItems
zhnSystemTrapItems.description: The collection of SNMP trap objects.

zhnSystemCommunityItems.name: zhnSystemCommunityItems
zhnSystemCommunityItems.description: The collection of SNMP community objects.

zhnSystemFixedCommunityItems.name: zhnSystemFixedCommunityItems
zhnSystemFixedCommunityItems.description: The collection of pre-provisioned SNMP community objects.

zhnSystemClockingItems.name: zhnSystemClockingItems
